sample.description:
Levi Strauss, American Eagle and Gap have leaned on A-list celebrities like Beyonce and Sydney Sweeney to drive denim sales, sparking a ‚Äúdenim war‚Äù in retail.

Levi, the company that invented jeans, reported that its Beyonc√© partnership earned $65 million in media value and contributed 12% growth in its women's business in its Q3 2025 earnings. Sydney Sweeney and girl group Katseye's viral campaigns for American Eagle and Gap are having similarly positive impacts on sales.

sample.title: Why U.S. workers are clinging to their jobs
sample.description:
Fewer Americans are quitting their jobs, and hiring has slowed, creating a frozen labor market with limited mobility.

Economic uncertainty is causing workers to stay put despite growing dissatisfaction.

sample.title: Waymo Leads The 2025 Robotaxi Surge As Zoox Expands And Tesla Races To Catch Up
sample.description:
Alphabet-owned Waymo scaled up and now leads the American robotaxi market by far, while Baidu-owned Apollo Go dominated in China. In the San Francisco Bay Area, there are now multiple robotaxi services operating, including Zoox and Waymo, although only Waymo provides commercial rides completely free of any human safety operators. Tesla finally launched their robotaxis in Austin and San Francisco but both states include human safety supervisors onboard ready to quickly take over driving. In December, Musk confirmed that driverless robotaxi tests had begun in Austin, which drove Tesla stock to a year high.

sample.description:
Private companies like OpenAI and SpaceX have captured enormous investor enthusiasm, driving up their valuations. Yet because they‚Äôre privately held, they‚Äôve remained largely inaccessible to retail investors.

Now a new approached called tokenization could change that by giving retail investors access to investments aligned with the performance of private companies. But some worry that tokenizing private companies could be a way to bypass longstanding regulations meant to protect investors.

sample.title: Why U.S. Shipbuilding Collapsed ‚Äî And The Push To Rebuild It
sample.description:
America used to be a world leader in shipbuilding. But with a shortage of talent, antiquated operating procedures and outdated facilities the industry ‚Äî essential to U.S. energy security and defense ‚Äî is in crisis. China dominates the global commercial shipbuilding industry accounting for 53% of global market share followed by South Korea and Japan. The U.S. accounts for about 0.1%. But that could soon change. In southern Philadelphia, $5 billion is being invested by South Korean shipping conglomerate Hanwha. It hopes to turn this decades old shipyard into a state of the art facility. To look at how shipyards are being revitalized, CNBC traveled to Wisconsin‚Äôs Great Lakes region and to one of America's oldest shipyards in Philadelphia.

sample.title: Fifa to arrive on Netflix | Global News Podcast
sample.description:
A brand new Fifa game is coming to Netflix in 2026, several years after its acrimonious split with developer EA.

The project, which is set to launch in time for next year's World Cup, is being developed and published by Delphi Interactive, makers of IO Interactive's James Bond project, 007: First Light.

It will be playable via smartphone, but reaction to the announcement has so far been mixed, with some fans questioning whether the mobile-first focus from Netflix was the way forward for the franchise.

We speak to our technology reporter Laura Cress.

sample.description:
A new batch of 68 photographs related to the late sex offender Jeffrey Epstein has been made public by Democratic US lawmakers.

sample.title: Teachers in England to be trained to spot misogyny | BBC News
sample.description:
Teachers will be given training to spot and tackle misogyny in the classroom, while high-risk pupils could be sent on behavioural courses as part of the UK government's long-awaited strategy to halve violence against women and girls in the next decade.
 
The ¬£20m package will include a new helpline for teenagers to get support for concerns about abuse in their own relationships.
 
Nearly 40% of teenagers in relationships are victims of abuse, domestic abuse charity Reducing the Risk has said.
 
The government hopes that by tackling the early roots of misogyny, it will prevent young men from becoming violent abusers.
 
But the domestic abuse commissioner for England and Wales, Dame Nicole Jacobs, said the commitments did "not go far enough" to see the number of people experiencing abuse start to fall.

sample.title: What's inside a secret missile factory ramping up Ukraine's weapons industry? | BBC News
sample.description:
The Ukrainian arms industry is ramping up production of its own weapons, despite hopes that US led peace talks could bring an end to the war.
 
After being heavily reliant on the west, Ukraine now says its producing more than 50% of the weapons it uses on the front line - that includes long range drones and missiles to hit targets deep inside Russia. 
 
The BBC's Defence Correspondent Jonathan Beale has been given rare access to one of the companies now mass producing these weapons ‚Äì which they say are the only way of providing Ukraine with reliable security guarantees.
